<span id="freeTextContainer12791545771865122652">In 1886 a shy, middle-aged piano tuner named Edgar Drake receives an unusual commission from the British War Office: to travel to the remote jungles of northeast Burma and there repair a rare piano belonging to an eccentric army surgeon who has proven mysteriously indispensable to the imperial design. From this irresistible beginning, <b>The Piano Tuner</b><i> </i>launches its protagoni</span>
  <span id="freeText12791545771865122652" style="display:none">In 1886 a shy, middle-aged piano tuner named Edgar Drake receives an unusual commission from the British War Office: to travel to the remote jungles of northeast Burma and there repair a rare piano belonging to an eccentric army surgeon who has proven mysteriously indispensable to the imperial design. From this irresistible beginning, <b>The Piano Tuner</b><i> </i>launches its protagonist into a world of seductive loveliness and nightmarish intrigue. And as he follows Drake’s journey, Mason dazzles readers with his erudition, moves them with his vibrantly rendered characters, and enmeshes them in the unbreakable spell of his storytelling.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12791545771865122652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

