<span id="freeTextContainer2703532846043504794">It is rare that I stop reading a book before the end. Usually I will read the whole thing and then come to the conclusion that it was a bad book, didn&apos;t need to read the book, etc.<br/><br/>I didn&apos;t need that long for this one. I have never taken so long to read 100 pages in my entire life. There is just no way that I can recommend this to someone, sorry. It reads like one of those books we hated in high school, and plods along like some 17th century English aristocrat who had to write something to make t</span>
  <span id="freeText2703532846043504794" style="display:none">It is rare that I stop reading a book before the end. Usually I will read the whole thing and then come to the conclusion that it was a bad book, didn't need to read the book, etc.<br /><br />I didn't need that long for this one. I have never taken so long to read 100 pages in my entire life. There is just no way that I can recommend this to someone, sorry. It reads like one of those books we hated in high school, and plods along like some 17th century English aristocrat who had to write something to make the schoolmarm happy.<br /><br />Sorry, I just cannot endorse this one. Pass it over, pass it up, pass it along. There are better things out there to read.</span>
