        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer25199474" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14452579970386275106">Being a pianist, I especially enjoyed this book. I loved the references to various preludes by Bach and the Haydn Sonata Op 50 in D Major (Youtube it!). When I finished the book, I found my WTC (Well-Tempered Clavier) and played Bach&apos;s Prelude #4, referenced on p. 248 in the novel. I think I will always remember it. I was a little disappointed in the ending, although, it added to the mysteriousness of the story and the haunting qualities throughout (Please don&apos;t let my disappointment keep you fr</span>
  <span id="freeText14452579970386275106" style="display:none">Being a pianist, I especially enjoyed this book. I loved the references to various preludes by Bach and the Haydn Sonata Op 50 in D Major (Youtube it!). When I finished the book, I found my WTC (Well-Tempered Clavier) and played Bach's Prelude #4, referenced on p. 248 in the novel. I think I will always remember it. I was a little disappointed in the ending, although, it added to the mysteriousness of the story and the haunting qualities throughout (Please don't let my disappointment keep you from reading the book). I also enjoyed the references to art and recalled reading The DaVinci Code and running to the computer to do a google search on particular paintings. This would be a good book club book. A number of good topics for discussion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14452579970386275106" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
