            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8507674-jan?shelf=2018">2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2496778724" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10210193940035445443">This is, indeed, a mesmerizing tale. I enjoyed it--could hardly put it down because it was so unusual, and I wondered where it would go. Late in the book there are delirious, hallucinatory scenes that are amazing. I am glad I read this book, admire the author tremendously, and wonder who else might like it. I think it helps to know a bit about piano music. I suspect it&apos;s this tale that nudged me to order some new sheet music and set a goal of playing my long-dormant piano this winter. Unusual st</span>
  <span id="freeText10210193940035445443" style="display:none">This is, indeed, a mesmerizing tale. I enjoyed it--could hardly put it down because it was so unusual, and I wondered where it would go. Late in the book there are delirious, hallucinatory scenes that are amazing. I am glad I read this book, admire the author tremendously, and wonder who else might like it. I think it helps to know a bit about piano music. I suspect it's this tale that nudged me to order some new sheet music and set a goal of playing my long-dormant piano this winter. Unusual story that reminded me a little bit of Jorge Luis Borges's details with a little Conrad "Heart of Darkness" to give shape to the narrative.</span>
