        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1849900230" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12505576039552716903">This was an interesting premise - a fairly staid piano tuner (Edgar Drake) is sent to Burma in 1886 to tune a piano belonging to a mysterious but important chap who is helping to protect British military interests. A bit of &quot;Apocalypse Now&quot; or &quot;Lawrence of Arabia&quot; with the mysterious Major Carroll working with the local tribes to try to establish some sort of peace settlement (or is he?).<br/>The first half of the book describes Drake&apos;s journey to the remote Burmese outpost. IN the secong half of the</span>
  <span id="freeText12505576039552716903" style="display:none">This was an interesting premise - a fairly staid piano tuner (Edgar Drake) is sent to Burma in 1886 to tune a piano belonging to a mysterious but important chap who is helping to protect British military interests. A bit of "Apocalypse Now" or "Lawrence of Arabia" with the mysterious Major Carroll working with the local tribes to try to establish some sort of peace settlement (or is he?).<br />The first half of the book describes Drake's journey to the remote Burmese outpost. IN the secong half of the book, he falls under Carroll's charisma and is enchanted by the lovely Khin Myo. He tunes the piano but does not leave.<br />There is lots of information on Burma in the 1880s, how to tune a piano and a critique on the impact of colonialism. It's a good read but not a great one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12505576039552716903" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


